Kernel System Calls
-------------------
//The stat system call is used to retrieve the meta data of the file
stat("./welcomeToDevOpsJan22", {st_mode=S_IFDIR|0700, st_size=4096, ...}) = 0

//The getrandom system call is used to generate random numbers for more secure way to obtain high quality numbers directly from the kernel
stat("./welcomeToDevOpsJan22", {st_mode=S_IFDIR|0700, st_size=4096, ...}) = 0

//The openat system call is used to open files or create file descriptors so we can see there's a file called "welcomeToDevOpsJan22/goodLuck" when i ran strace.
openat(AT_FDCWD, "welcomeToDevOpsJan22/goodLuck", O_WRONLY|O_CREAT|O_TRUNC, 0666) = 3

//The write system call is used to write data to files or devices
write(3, "There you go... tell me what I d"..., 36) = 36

//And once we are done, the close system call followed by exit group system call are exiting the program with a return code of 0 because it went successfully
close(3)                                = 0
+++ exited with 0 +++

So first of all i ran sudo chmod u+x on the file so we can execute it and then
the program created a new directory (welcomeToDevOpsJan22) which contain a file called (goodLuck) and in the text file it says "There you go... Tell me what i do"
