Binary Numbers
--------------
1.צפיתי בסרטון הזה כדי להבין איך לחשב:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VLflTjd3lWA&ab_channel=TheOrganicChemistryTutor

111 in binary equals to 7 in decimal
100 in binary equals to 4 in decimal
10110 in binary equals to 22 in decimal

2.The range is from 0 to 2^8 - 1 = 0 to 255

3.
For negative numbers (-1 to -256): Use Two's complement representation.
Start with the positive binary representation of the number.
Invert all the bits (change 0s to 1s and 1s to 0s).
Add 1 to the inverted binary number.

For example:
Binary representation of 5 positive : 00000101
Then we invert the bits and get the following: 11111010
And then add 1 to the inverted binary number: 11111011
So now the 9-bit two complement method representation of -5 is 11111011.

4.
I used the following format to understand how to calculate
SIIII.FFFF
S is the sign bit (0 for positive, 1 for negative).
IIII is the 4-bit integer part.
FFFF is the 4-bit fractional part.

Now if we represent the decimal number 12.75:
Convert the integer part (12) to binary: 1100
Then convert the fractional part (0.75) to binary: 0.11 (75% of 1)
Then combine the integer and fractional parts: 1100.11
And then Adjust to the 8bit format: 01100.1100
so now in an 8bit representation 12.75 would be 01100.1100

And thank god to the internet and calculators....